The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Sunday, May 30, 2004  Fine Print				 				 				 																Monster meal																																	Dhaka, May 29 (AFP): Bangladeshi-born celebrity chef Tommy Miah cooked hundreds of kilograms of lentils and meat in Dhaka in a bid to gain entry into the Guinness Book of Records for preparing the largest-ever meal, a report said today.																																	Miah, known as Britains Curry King after the success of his Raj restaurant in the Scottish capital Edinburgh, set a record for cooking the worlds biggest curry in 1994.																																	Over 2,000 children gathered at a Dhaka park yesterday to join Miah in cooking halim the New Age newspaper reported.																																	To prepare the monster meal, he and the children mixed 120 kg of lentils, 100 kg of meat, 240 litres of water, 130 kg of vegetables, 56 kg of flour and 70 kg of herbs in a massive pot. Theres enough halim here for at least 5,000, said Miah. 
